description:
Introduce the execution substrate type abstraction that all subsequent work depends on.

## What to implement

In `packages/pi-beadwork-extension/src/types.ts`:

```ts
type WorkerExecutionMode = "current-branch" | "worktree";

type CurrentBranchCheckout = {
  executionMode: "current-branch";
  checkoutPath: string;    // repo root / current checkout
  branchName: string;      // branch recorded at launch
  launchHead: string;      // required: attribution search starts here
};

type WorktreeCheckout = {
  executionMode: "worktree";
  checkoutPath: string;    // worker worktree path
  branchName: string;
  worktreePath: string;
};

type WorkerCheckout = CurrentBranchCheckout | WorktreeCheckout;
```

Update `WorkerRuntime` to incorporate `WorkerCheckout` via intersection:
```ts
type BaseWorkerRuntime = { workerId, ticketId, epicId?, /* existing fields */ };
type WorkerRuntime = BaseWorkerRuntime & WorkerCheckout;
```

## Design Rules

- `executionMode` is THE discriminant — use it in all type narrowing
- `worktreePath` only exists on `WorktreeCheckout` — do NOT include it as optional on `CurrentBranchCheckout`
- `launchHead` is required on `CurrentBranchCheckout` — it must always be recorded at launch
- Current-branch workers must NOT fake `worktreePath = repoRoot`
- Export type guards: `isCurrentBranchWorker(w)` and `isWorktreeWorker(w)`
- Keep backward compat with existing `WorkerRuntime` consumers via the union intersection

## Tests

- Type guard correctness with both checkout shapes
- Compile-time impossible-state tests (accessing `worktreePath` on current-branch should be type error)
- Serialization/deserialization round-trip for both shapes

## Definition of Done

- Types compile cleanly with strict TypeScript
- Existing code using `WorkerRuntime` still compiles (possibly with narrowing changes needed later)
- Type guards exported and tested
- lint/test/typecheck pass clean
